WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:03.752
<i>Man". Previously on Revolution...</i>

00:05.000 --> 00:07.230
Have you ever been
to Spring City, Oklahoma?

00:07.440 --> 00:09.078
It has to be important,
or he wouldn't have said it.

00:09.240 --> 00:11.709
Aaron, I just want you
to know how sorry I am.

00:11.880 --> 00:14.793
Don't apologize to me.
Apologize to her.

00:14.960 --> 00:18.237
I am not going back to being
some lame housewife, Tom.

00:18.400 --> 00:19.879
<i>There is a life that you promised me,</i>

00:20.080 --> 00:21.878
<i>and I have sacrificed
a hell of a lot to get it.</i>

00:22.080 --> 00:24.117
Just so you know,
once we get what we want,

00:24.280 --> 00:26.032
<i>I am going to take a knife,
and I am going to gut</i>

00:26.200 --> 00:28.396
<i>that Chief of Staff husband of yours.</i>

00:28.560 --> 00:30.392
<i>Sebastian: You took my son to Mexico?</i>

00:30.560 --> 00:32.436
- Afternoon, folks.
- You're Connor?

00:32.600 --> 00:34.511
- Who the hell are you?
- I'm your dad.

00:34.720 --> 00:37.439
You are a Monroe.
You should be leading the Republic.

00:37.640 --> 00:40.439
You and me.
Together, we can take it back.

00:40.640 --> 00:41.835
I'm gonna have to take a rain check.

00:42.000 --> 00:44.469
- Mr. Nufiez wants to meet you.
- Rachel: Let me guess...

00:44.640 --> 00:46.631
we're gonna get ourselves
killed saving Monroe?

00:46.800 --> 00:47.949
Aren't you glad you came?

00:48.120 --> 00:49.599
<i>Aaron". What the hell is going on?</i>

00:49.760 --> 00:52.274
Why here?
What does any of this mean?

00:52.400 --> 00:53.629
Aaron?

00:55.600 --> 00:56.999
Grace?

01:07.400 --> 01:08.959
Grace, what are you doing here?

01:10.400 --> 01:11.799
I live here, Aaron.

01:13.600 --> 01:15.034
Alone.

01:17.080 --> 01:18.718
Ever since the tower.

01:20.240 --> 01:22.754
I've been trying to forget about all that,
to tell you the truth.

01:25.520 --> 01:27.830
Now, you want to tell me
what you're doing here?

01:28.720 --> 01:30.677
I think I was sent here to find you.

01:32.160 --> 01:33.514
Find me?

01:36.480 --> 01:38.630
This day just keeps getting weirder.

01:42.200 --> 01:43.270
Come on.

01:49.360 --> 01:51.670
She walked in late yesterday.

01:51.880 --> 01:54.349
Said it took her more
than a week to get here,

01:54.520 --> 01:56.875
then dropped like a stone
from heatstroke.

02:22.560 --> 02:24.153
Priscilla.

02:26.280 --> 02:27.714
Aaron?

02:32.080 --> 02:33.514
You know her?

02:35.120 --> 02:37.077
She was my wife.

02:42.400 --> 02:44.471
(DOG BARKING)

02:48.960 --> 02:50.439
Sebastian: You're making a mistake.

02:50.760 --> 02:52.558
You still trying to sell that?

02:55.000 --> 02:56.832
You and me are gonna be
kings of the world, huh?

02:57.000 --> 02:58.434
Could've been...

02:58.600 --> 03:01.194
...if you didn't have your head
crammed so firmly up your ass.

03:05.480 --> 03:06.834
(CONNOR SHOUTS IN SPANISH)

03:09.560 --> 03:12.951
♪ (BAND PLAYING
"BORN TO BE WILD" IN SPANISH) ♪

03:26.400 --> 03:28.152
(LAUGHTER)

03:33.040 --> 03:34.792
(FLIES BUZZING)

03:37.080 --> 03:38.798
What'd he do?

03:39.640 --> 03:41.313
Didn't do his job.

03:53.680 --> 03:56.274
I can't believe we have to rescue
that son of a bitch.

03:57.160 --> 03:59.470
I know. I know.

04:06.280 --> 04:07.793
Wow.

04:08.400 --> 04:10.596
Your boss has really nice taste.

04:11.400 --> 04:14.438
It's like Donald Trump
threw up on Scarf ace.

04:16.680 --> 04:18.353
Man: Connor...

04:18.440 --> 04:19.589
(SPEAKING IN SPANISH)

04:38.840 --> 04:40.513
Sebastian Monroe.

04:41.680 --> 04:44.559
It really is you standing here
in my house.

04:48.720 --> 04:51.030
It's an honor to meet you.

04:53.720 --> 04:55.757
(DRY CHUCKLE)
Yeah?

04:56.840 --> 04:58.797
I can imagine the thrill.

05:00.240 --> 05:01.878
So, it's incredible.

05:02.400 --> 05:04.676
Connor here is your blood.

05:08.680 --> 05:09.670
That's right.

05:10.680 --> 05:13.991
You know, I always knew
he was special somehow.

05:14.160 --> 05:16.390
I knew it from
the first time I saw him.

05:16.560 --> 05:21.077
Took him off the street,
gave him a home... My home.

05:22.000 --> 05:25.231
I practically raised him,
and now look at him.

05:26.520 --> 05:28.557
He's my right hand.

05:30.520 --> 05:33.592
That's touching, really. So, uh...

05:35.320 --> 05:36.594
...what are you gonna do with me?

05:41.200 --> 05:42.873
What do you think, Connor?

05:43.440 --> 05:45.909
What should we do
with your dear old dad?

05:50.240 --> 05:53.278
I say... we sell him.

05:54.040 --> 05:55.553
To the highest bidder.

05:55.880 --> 05:57.757
Texas, Mexico...

06:01.760 --> 06:04.878
Someone's gonna pay a lot
for his sorry ass.

06:32.640 --> 06:34.278
What are they building?

06:34.440 --> 06:35.794
And why so fast?

06:36.800 --> 06:39.792
I don't know. It's in the middle of nowhere.
It's all fenced in.

06:41.120 --> 06:44.397
Options start at prison.

06:45.160 --> 06:46.992
Only get worse from there.

06:49.560 --> 06:51.870
Oh, no. No. No.

06:52.520 --> 06:53.510
What?

06:54.120 --> 06:55.679
That's Lloyd Welliver.

06:58.400 --> 07:00.073
He's a friend of mine.

07:01.200 --> 07:02.838
A good friend.

07:04.520 --> 07:06.238
- We got to go get him.
- Whoa.

07:07.160 --> 07:09.356
That's an armed camp.
There are two of us.

07:09.880 --> 07:11.359
How do you think we're gonna get in?

07:17.080 --> 07:20.357
Place that in the other room.
Thank you.

07:21.720 --> 07:23.199
Tom: Ma'am?

07:27.640 --> 07:29.358
Congratulations on you
and your husband's

07:29.520 --> 07:31.397
new position as Chief of Staff.

07:31.640 --> 07:34.792
Compliments of Commander Allenford.

07:35.520 --> 07:37.830
Please convey my thanks
to the commander.

07:42.280 --> 07:44.476
Here. Thank you.

07:48.320 --> 07:51.870
I was wondering if you had a chance
to talk to your husband yet

07:52.040 --> 07:54.395
about my desire to join
his security detail.

07:56.200 --> 07:58.430
Well, it's just my first day,
but when the time is right,

07:58.600 --> 08:00.557
- I'll...
- Time is right for what?

08:01.920 --> 08:03.194
Oh, nothing, dear.

08:03.360 --> 08:07.957
Just a... social invitation
from Commander Allenford.

08:08.600 --> 08:09.556
Mmm.

08:09.720 --> 08:13.315
Wait till you see the gift
that we... well, you...

08:13.480 --> 08:15.357
- received from the president.
- Oh?

08:15.520 --> 08:19.036
Julia: It's a quill pen
that once belonged to John Adams.

08:32.320 --> 08:34.789
- Hey, you got to take a look at this.
- Not now.

08:36.440 --> 08:37.999
Now.

08:42.720 --> 08:44.393
Where the hell did you get this?

08:44.560 --> 08:47.552
Out of Allenford's room. Look!

08:51.240 --> 08:54.392
Reeducation programs,
same kind I was in...

08:54.560 --> 08:56.119
they're opening more.

08:56.960 --> 08:58.109
Scranton, Pennsylvania,

08:58.280 --> 09:00.271
Willoughby, Texas,
Clearvvater, Florida, everywhere.

09:01.320 --> 09:03.277
Guess who's behind it.

09:03.440 --> 09:07.877
My new stepdad, Doyle.
He runs the whole thing.

09:08.040 --> 09:09.951
What the hell do you
want me to do about it?

09:10.120 --> 09:13.351
Something, anything.

09:13.520 --> 09:16.433
After what that program did to me...

09:18.800 --> 09:20.757
...pretty much the guy who
screwed me is screwing Mom.

09:20.920 --> 09:22.558
Watch your mouth.

09:23.840 --> 09:25.990
You're just gonna let this stand?

09:37.760 --> 09:39.398
(LAUGHTER)

09:57.360 --> 10:00.398
♪ (PLAYING "BLACK BETTY"
IN SPANISH) ♪

10:19.080 --> 10:20.070
Hey.

10:21.040 --> 10:22.599
(MAN SPEAKING SPANISH)

10:22.920 --> 10:25.958
Uh...
(SPEAKS BROKEN SPANISH)

10:28.240 --> 10:29.753
Hey.

10:31.200 --> 10:33.396
(BLOWS LANDING)
(GLASS BREAKING)

10:39.080 --> 10:40.798
Are you...

10:41.920 --> 10:43.354
...really here?

10:43.840 --> 10:45.638
(DRY CHUCKLE)

10:48.640 --> 10:51.234
I could ask you the same thing.

10:53.160 --> 10:55.515
It's hard to know what's real.

10:57.920 --> 10:59.274
My father...

11:00.320 --> 11:01.913
...said I had to come.

11:03.560 --> 11:05.710
Your dead father?

11:09.720 --> 11:11.233
I don't believe this.

11:12.400 --> 11:15.279
- I'm going crazy.
- No.

11:16.880 --> 11:18.791
That's not what I mean.
I mean...

11:20.800 --> 11:23.155
...it's happening to you too,
of all people.

11:25.840 --> 11:27.114
What?

11:28.840 --> 11:30.638
I've been seeing things.

11:32.320 --> 11:34.118
People who aren't there.

11:36.880 --> 11:39.474
- Fireflies--
- You've seen the fireflies?

11:45.800 --> 11:47.313
(VOICE TREMBLING) I was sure...

11:49.600 --> 11:51.955
...I was losing my mind.

11:53.480 --> 11:55.039
That I was...

11:56.160 --> 11:57.639
Look at me.

12:01.120 --> 12:02.872
You're not crazy.

12:10.360 --> 12:13.512
Aaron, none of this makes...

12:14.640 --> 12:15.914
...any sense.

12:17.360 --> 12:19.192
Not yet.

12:35.520 --> 12:38.239
Out by the pool,
I swear I saw empanadas.

12:38.440 --> 12:40.351
You'll have to make do.

12:40.520 --> 12:42.193
We only need to keep you
alive a couple of days,

12:42.400 --> 12:44.550
till we find a buyer for you.

12:45.560 --> 12:47.949
Look, I know I am...

12:48.160 --> 12:50.515
...completely screwed, okay?

12:52.880 --> 12:54.678
But I got to warn you.

12:54.840 --> 12:57.559
Warn me?
What, I should be scared of you?

12:57.720 --> 12:59.233
Not me.

13:00.880 --> 13:05.317
This guy Nufiez...
I've seen a thousand psychos like him.

13:05.480 --> 13:08.199
You should get as far
away from him as you can.

13:09.720 --> 13:13.839
When my aunt and uncle died,
I was alone, starving.

13:14.000 --> 13:17.152
Nobody cared.
Nobody even looked at me...

13:18.680 --> 13:20.398
...except for him.

13:21.480 --> 13:23.551
He treated me like I was his son.

13:25.960 --> 13:27.394
He's not your blood.

13:28.880 --> 13:32.396
Yeah, he's nice to you,
'cause that keeps you on the hook.

13:33.240 --> 13:34.913
The minute you screw up,

13:35.120 --> 13:37.236
you're gonna be strung up
and whipped to death too.

13:37.400 --> 13:40.472
Yeah?
Well, I'm not gonna screw up.

13:40.640 --> 13:42.551
(BLOW LANDS)

13:49.080 --> 13:50.275
Let's get out of here.

13:59.920 --> 14:01.638
You got to go, Miles.

14:02.840 --> 14:04.478
What?

14:05.400 --> 14:06.913
What are you doing?

14:07.080 --> 14:10.436
Look, if I get away,
it's on the kid, all right?

14:10.920 --> 14:13.196
Nufiez is gonna hurt him,
maybe even kill him.

14:13.600 --> 14:15.910
Right. What do you think's
gonna happen to you?

14:16.120 --> 14:18.191
He's my son, Miles.

14:19.680 --> 14:21.000
I'm not leaving.

14:21.760 --> 14:24.036
Hey! Hey!

14:25.040 --> 14:26.314
(SHOUTING IN SPANISH)

14:26.480 --> 14:28.039
(BELL CLANGING)

14:28.200 --> 14:30.271
Go. Go!

14:50.080 --> 14:51.593
You're a hero, kid.

14:53.200 --> 14:54.838
I was trying to escape.

14:56.160 --> 14:57.559
You caught me.

15:01.680 --> 15:04.752
I don't understand.
Why are you doing this?

15:11.760 --> 15:14.320
(MAN SHOUTS)
(SHOTS RINGING)

15:14.480 --> 15:16.949
(GRUNTING)

15:38.240 --> 15:39.560
You're a dick.

15:46.520 --> 15:48.033
Charlie: Who would have thought?

15:48.400 --> 15:50.357
Between the two of us,
you're the crazy one.

15:51.040 --> 15:52.553
Maybe you didn't hear me.

15:53.880 --> 15:55.279
Lloyd's a friend.

15:55.440 --> 15:57.078
0K8)'-

15:57.880 --> 16:01.350
And we'll get him back
when Miles and the others get here.

16:02.360 --> 16:03.919
It might be too late by then.

16:04.080 --> 16:06.754
You're right.
It might be.

16:07.760 --> 16:11.799
But getting yourself captured
or killed isn't gonna help anybody.

16:11.960 --> 16:13.314
That's not gonna happen.

16:13.480 --> 16:15.357
The place is crawling
with troops, Grandpa.

16:15.520 --> 16:16.715
You're not a soldier. You're- -

16:16.880 --> 16:18.234
I'm old?

16:19.440 --> 16:23.115
Not too old to smack
a little respect into you.

16:27.680 --> 16:31.230
Look, I understand the Patriots,
all that.

16:32.880 --> 16:35.349
You feel like it's your fault.

16:35.520 --> 16:37.113
You want to make it right.

16:38.160 --> 16:39.992
I see where Mom gets it from.

16:41.760 --> 16:45.230
And you know how that's
always worked out for her.

17:00.640 --> 17:03.075
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

17:19.040 --> 17:21.111
(ORDERS IN SPANISH)

17:24.560 --> 17:26.233
What was I supposed to do?
He's my son.

17:26.440 --> 17:27.874
Oh, shut up.

17:28.040 --> 17:29.792
You've been his dad for five minutes.

17:29.960 --> 17:31.473
Now all of a sudden,
you're Cliff Huxtable?

17:31.640 --> 17:33.313
You wouldn't do the same for Charlie?

17:34.880 --> 17:38.191
Look... I saw the kid in trouble.

17:38.360 --> 17:39.998
I couldn't leave him, all right?

17:41.080 --> 17:43.435
I don't know, maybe this gives him a
step up with his boss, something I...

17:43.600 --> 17:47.150
What do I have to give him, huh?
What have I got to give him, Miles?

17:47.320 --> 17:48.799
I got nothing.

17:50.120 --> 17:53.829
- So I gave him me.
- Yeah. Well, you gave him me, too.

17:55.640 --> 17:59.998
I cannot believe
the first selfless act of your entire life

18:00.160 --> 18:02.151
is the one that screws me, too.

18:03.120 --> 18:04.679
Thank you.

18:07.280 --> 18:10.079
Lower your voice.
What if someone hears?

18:10.240 --> 18:13.596
Julia, your husband's responsible

18:13.760 --> 18:16.274
for putting your son
through a world of hurt.

18:16.440 --> 18:19.478
And I hate him for it,
but we have got to stick to the plan.

18:19.640 --> 18:22.792
All you have to do is get me
into his office, into his files,

18:22.960 --> 18:26.032
- and I will find what I need there.
- To blackmail him?

18:26.200 --> 18:28.635
To get the promotion that you've
been dangling in front of me.

18:28.800 --> 18:31.189
What if he finds out?
You could ruin everything.

18:32.600 --> 18:36.878
Well... then you tell me.

18:37.680 --> 18:39.751
What is the plan?

18:40.880 --> 18:45.636
For you to stay nestled
in that soft feather bed of his?

18:45.800 --> 18:49.031
Everything that I am doing

18:49.200 --> 18:50.952
I am doing to protect you.

18:51.120 --> 18:53.873
Well, from where I'm sitting...

18:55.840 --> 18:58.514
...maybe you like
the power he's giving you.

18:59.720 --> 19:01.870
Maybe you like
what else he's giving you, too.

19:05.280 --> 19:06.634
Torn...

19:07.560 --> 19:11.633
If you go anywhere near his office...

19:13.320 --> 19:15.197
...I'm not sure...

19:16.040 --> 19:18.316
...that I can protect you.

19:20.240 --> 19:21.560
Can't?

19:22.920 --> 19:24.035
Or won't?

19:30.920 --> 19:33.958
♪ (PLAYING "LIVING AFTER MIDNIGHT") ♪

19:47.560 --> 19:49.358
I'm gonna go get a drink.

20:17.480 --> 20:20.074
(NUNEZ SPEAKING SPANISH)

21:05.840 --> 21:07.194
Hmm...

21:58.000 --> 22:01.197
(CHEERING)

22:17.240 --> 22:18.560
Don't go easy.

22:43.280 --> 22:44.270
(GRUNTS)

22:54.960 --> 22:57.076
(EXCLAIMING)

23:05.800 --> 23:07.950
(EXHALING)

23:08.680 --> 23:11.399
Do we want to sell him or bury him?

24:03.200 --> 24:06.397
Okay, look, I've told
her everything I know,

24:06.560 --> 24:08.551
but we've still got
a lot of questions.

24:09.480 --> 24:11.312
Like why you're both here.

24:12.600 --> 24:16.514
It's 'cause the nano told
you to come, am I right?

24:19.560 --> 24:21.358
How do you know that?

24:21.560 --> 24:22.675
(CHUCKLES)

24:22.840 --> 24:25.912
I was always afraid that maybe
one day they could wake up.

24:26.080 --> 24:27.718
How'd they wake up?

24:29.320 --> 24:34.554
What's the brain, besides a cloud
of neurons all talking to each other?

24:34.720 --> 24:36.836
You get enough of 'em together...

24:37.760 --> 24:39.592
You cross into consciousness.

24:40.920 --> 24:43.833
There are more nanites than
there are neurons in a brain.

24:46.080 --> 24:47.798
<i>In a million brains.</i>

24:49.760 --> 24:52.673
<i>So, if they learn to network...</i>

24:53.920 --> 24:56.434
That's a big-ass brain.

24:56.640 --> 24:59.837
But it still doesn't explain...
why us.

25:04.360 --> 25:06.829
It's the code you wrote, Aaron.

25:07.920 --> 25:09.433
The one we stole.

25:10.560 --> 25:14.269
We didn't just use it for the tower.
We put it in the nano too.

25:15.600 --> 25:17.352
You what?

25:18.560 --> 25:22.349
Me, Rachel, Warren...
we built its body.

25:23.040 --> 25:24.599
But you gave it its mind.

25:27.280 --> 25:29.032
And let me guess.

25:30.760 --> 25:32.159
You had some help.

25:32.920 --> 25:35.878
Yeah, it was my thesis,
but, yeah, Priscilla helped.

25:36.880 --> 25:38.359
So that's why you.

25:39.800 --> 25:40.995
Like anybody,

25:41.160 --> 25:44.198
damn thing just wants
to know who its parents are.

25:46.280 --> 25:49.636
Our friend Peter... he helped, too.

25:54.000 --> 25:56.469
I wonder why he wasn't called, too.

25:56.640 --> 25:58.199
This is just...

26:00.560 --> 26:02.790
This is a lot to take in.

26:04.040 --> 26:05.838
You think that's a lot?

26:07.520 --> 26:09.636
Try wrapping your head around this:

26:09.800 --> 26:11.950
This thing is everywhere.

26:12.120 --> 26:15.192
And apparently,
it's got a mind of its own.

26:15.880 --> 26:17.712
Yeah.

26:17.880 --> 26:21.475
Aaron, how is that
any different from God?

26:25.880 --> 26:28.440
(INDISTINCT SHOUTS)

26:50.600 --> 26:52.637
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

27:14.520 --> 27:16.318
(EXHALES)
Oh, hell.

27:17.360 --> 27:18.395
Lloyd.

27:19.120 --> 27:21.031
(GUN COCKING)
Who are you?

27:22.000 --> 27:24.514
- Just hold on.
- Step out slow.

27:31.240 --> 27:33.436
I work here.
I'm on the night shift.

27:33.600 --> 27:35.989
Yeah, well, you're coming with me.
(GRUNTS)

27:36.960 --> 27:39.429
How... How did you know I was here?

27:39.600 --> 27:42.160
Because you're exactly like Mom.
Neither of you listen.

27:42.320 --> 27:44.391
Come on, drop him.

28:09.200 --> 28:11.191
Freeze!

28:15.440 --> 28:16.999
Stop right there!

28:54.320 --> 28:55.640
(GASPS)

28:57.120 --> 28:58.758
It's you.

29:00.400 --> 29:04.109
You found this in the main kitchen
under the butcher's block.

29:04.720 --> 29:06.597
You went downstairs.

29:07.360 --> 29:08.839
You let them out.

29:10.280 --> 29:13.318
You never saw me.

29:15.160 --> 29:16.434
Why are you doing this?

29:18.400 --> 29:20.038
He did it for me.

29:31.840 --> 29:34.195
So it turns out
a thesis project from MIT

29:34.360 --> 29:37.352
makes you mother
of the world's first A.l.

29:37.520 --> 29:39.318
Welcome to the SyFy Channel.

29:45.000 --> 29:47.230
Maybe you were better off
thinking you were crazy.

29:47.400 --> 29:50.597
No. That was much worse.

29:52.040 --> 29:53.189
I felt like...

29:54.560 --> 29:56.358
...like I lost my grip.

29:58.720 --> 30:00.438
My sanity-

30:02.200 --> 30:03.918
And I was scared.

30:05.040 --> 30:08.317
My husband... couldn't handle it.

30:10.640 --> 30:13.314
He took the kids and left.

30:18.480 --> 30:19.993
What about you?

30:31.240 --> 30:33.470
I thought I was going crazy, too.

30:42.240 --> 30:43.913
I had someone, too.

30:46.840 --> 30:48.399
She didn't leave.

30:50.040 --> 30:52.236
She stood by me through all of it.

30:56.440 --> 30:58.875
She stood by me and she died for it.

31:08.760 --> 31:10.512
What do we do now?

31:29.040 --> 31:32.032
I told you I do not know
who had access to the...

31:32.240 --> 31:34.038
I just moved in, damn it.

31:38.880 --> 31:40.598
Victor, what...
What happened?

31:41.760 --> 31:43.159
Someone broke into my office.

31:43.320 --> 31:45.391
They went through all my files,
through everything.

31:45.560 --> 31:47.437
Any idea who?

31:49.760 --> 31:52.229
Don't worry, okay?
I'll get us more security.

31:54.120 --> 31:57.158
Whoever did this...
we'll find him.

31:57.960 --> 31:59.598
Come here.

32:03.280 --> 32:05.920
(PAINED BREATHING)

32:12.560 --> 32:14.517
So your kid did this to you.

32:15.520 --> 32:16.840
Sebastian: Yeah.

32:17.000 --> 32:19.071
I guess I should've hugged him more.

32:25.040 --> 32:26.189
What are you doing here?

32:28.200 --> 32:29.190
Move.

32:29.360 --> 32:31.590
Keys. Where'd you get keys?

32:32.880 --> 32:34.029
Your son.

32:50.840 --> 32:53.150
Stop!
It's enough.

32:54.520 --> 32:55.954
Put it down now.

33:06.840 --> 33:08.558
Just let him go.

33:09.640 --> 33:12.029
He slipped that bitch a key.

33:14.400 --> 33:16.391
Actually thought he could
get away with it.

33:16.560 --> 33:18.392
I'm sorry. I wasn't thinking.

33:18.560 --> 33:20.949
Loyalty doesn't need to think.

33:25.520 --> 33:27.716
Don't... Don't...

33:28.600 --> 33:30.671
Don't hurt him, all right?

33:32.280 --> 33:34.237
I have to hurt him now
because of you,

33:34.400 --> 33:37.472
'cause he tried to take you from me.

33:37.640 --> 33:39.790
And you, I own.

33:42.840 --> 33:45.275
I thought you said he
was like a son to you.

33:45.440 --> 33:46.669
He is.

33:47.400 --> 33:49.118
He has broken my heart.

33:50.680 --> 33:52.432
I took care of you.

33:53.960 --> 33:56.270
And you have chosen him over me.

33:59.080 --> 34:00.957
Let's just talk about this.

34:03.800 --> 34:05.199
I'm sorry, kid.

34:05.360 --> 34:07.874
But you know better than anyone

34:08.040 --> 34:11.112
that I can't have people
thinking I'm weak.

34:18.120 --> 34:20.077
Well, I'll tell you...

34:20.280 --> 34:22.271
...you know who obsesses
about weakness?

34:23.239 --> 34:24.753
Weak people.

34:30.679 --> 34:33.399
<i>Adios, Connor.</i>

34:42.080 --> 34:43.353
(GRUNTING)

34:57.040 --> 34:58.474
(GASPS)
Hey.

35:13.360 --> 35:16.318
- Well, he's pretty good, huh?
- Shut up and focus.

35:24.440 --> 35:25.714
Come on.

35:36.880 --> 35:40.350
(MEN SHOUTING, DISTANT)

35:40.520 --> 35:42.352
Come on, let's go!

35:44.160 --> 35:45.389
Let's go.

36:14.280 --> 36:17.796
That was pretty stupid back there,

36:17.960 --> 36:20.520
sticking your neck out
like that... I just, uh...

36:22.920 --> 36:25.480
- I just wanted to say...
- Go to hell.

36:25.640 --> 36:27.836
Take it easy, all right?
My back.

36:28.680 --> 36:31.194
Helping you was the
worst mistake of my life.

36:31.360 --> 36:32.794
I lost everything I had
'cause of you.

36:33.560 --> 36:34.630
You're welcome.

36:44.200 --> 36:47.431
- You think you can get it back?
- What?

36:49.960 --> 36:52.634
Everything you pissed away.

36:52.800 --> 36:55.269
Your army, your republic.

36:56.320 --> 36:59.039
One, I can do
whatever the hell I want.

36:59.200 --> 37:01.350
That's the way it's always been.

37:02.120 --> 37:03.394
Two...

37:06.320 --> 37:08.311
...we're gonna get it back.

37:09.160 --> 37:12.516
You and me, together.

37:16.800 --> 37:18.438
Good.

37:20.160 --> 37:22.117
But you better be telling the truth.

37:23.360 --> 37:24.873
Okay, first we got to mop up

37:25.040 --> 37:28.317
some of these red, white
and blue cockroaches,

37:28.480 --> 37:29.709
but you stick with me.

37:32.680 --> 37:34.717
We're just getting started.

37:45.000 --> 37:46.593
(JULIA CLEARS THROAT)

37:50.560 --> 37:52.836
Are you lost, ma'am?

37:54.200 --> 37:55.873
A word, Captain.

37:57.400 --> 37:59.232
What were you thinking, Tom?

37:59.400 --> 38:01.038
I don't know
what you're talking about.

38:01.200 --> 38:03.191
Don't give me that poker face.
Evening.

38:03.360 --> 38:04.998
You broke into his office.

38:05.160 --> 38:08.039
This "poker face" is my face.

38:10.400 --> 38:12.630
And I don't know
what you're talking about.

38:15.520 --> 38:17.238
It wasn't you.

38:18.600 --> 38:19.829
Well, then who was...

38:31.840 --> 38:34.309
What did you do, boy?
Did you break into Doyle's office?

38:34.480 --> 38:36.756
The two of you... you're scheming.

38:36.920 --> 38:39.309
You're tearing into each
other and everybody else.

38:39.480 --> 38:42.393
You don't even care that the world
is burning down around you.

38:44.280 --> 38:47.557
Yeah...
I dug into his office. I had to.

38:47.760 --> 38:50.274
They're gonna know it's you, Jason.
Oh, my God.

38:51.360 --> 38:52.680
You know what else I also found out?

38:52.840 --> 38:55.116
The reprogramming
is just the beginning.

38:55.280 --> 38:57.078
Dad, it's so much worse.

38:57.240 --> 38:58.958
They're gonna start
wiping people out.

38:59.120 --> 39:01.430
We have to think, Jason.
We have to get you out of here.

39:01.600 --> 39:03.910
No, you're not listening to me.

39:04.080 --> 39:06.515
- Jason.
- You're a damn fool.

39:06.680 --> 39:08.671
(APPROACHING VOICES)

39:11.880 --> 39:13.598
Jason Neville.

39:19.120 --> 39:21.634
- Come with us, son.
- Tom: Why?

39:21.800 --> 39:23.393
What is this about?

39:24.760 --> 39:26.637
Do you want me to start
asking you questions?

40:01.640 --> 40:03.233
Ed...

40:05.280 --> 40:06.953
Please, just let her go.

40:14.960 --> 40:16.758
Bring 'em with me.

40:36.000 --> 40:38.196
If you're gonna kill us,
just kill us.

40:38.560 --> 40:40.198
You'll need these.

40:49.680 --> 40:52.433
(SOFT COUGHING)

41:23.680 --> 41:25.318
What's happening?

41:28.880 --> 41:30.473
They have typhus.

41:32.000 --> 41:34.230
We had one case three days ago.

41:35.240 --> 41:37.072
Lloyd Welliver.

41:39.400 --> 41:40.913
Now we have four.

41:41.640 --> 41:42.869
So...

41:44.960 --> 41:47.076
...we're just trying to get ready.

41:47.240 --> 41:48.833
As fast as we can.

41:49.480 --> 41:51.039
So that's what
you're building out here.

41:51.200 --> 41:52.759
This is a quarantine camp.

41:57.000 --> 41:58.877
This is an outbreak.

42:01.760 --> 42:03.831
Look, I know we have our differences.

42:04.040 --> 42:06.270
But we have one thing in common...

42:07.400 --> 42:08.674
...this town.

42:11.560 --> 42:13.392
And if we don't work together...

42:15.400 --> 42:17.038
...we're gonna lose it.

42:56.760 --> 42:58.353
(English - SDH)
